# AGP Studios â€” Architecture Overview

Components
- Launcher (AGP_Studios)
  - Desktop app: library, downloads, installs, updates, launcher, AI chat UI.
  - Updater: self-update and package delta updates.
  - Local sandbox runner for generated servers.

- CMS (AGP_CMS)
  - REST APIs for users, catalog, builds, assets.
  - Authentication (OAuth2) and publisher accounts.
  - Asset storage (S3-compatible).

- Game Server Templates (AGP_GameServer)
  - Versioned server templates and runtime libraries.
  - Health, admin, match/session APIs.

- AGP_AI (Ashat)
  - Agent service for scaffolding, code generation, and patch application.
  - Action endpoints for generating diffs/PRs.

Data model (brief)
- User { id, username, email, password_hash, created_at }
- LibraryItem { id, slug, name, description, versions[] }
- Version { id, version, artifact_url, manifest }
- GameServerTemplate { id, name, description, repo_url, sample_builds }
- Session { id, host_user_id, players[], server_instance_id, state }

Realtime
- SignalR (presence, chat, matchmaking)
- WebSocket fallback for non-.NET clients

Security
- OAuth2 / JWT for authentication
- API scopes for publishing and server management
- Agent sandboxing + user approval for applied patches

Deployment
- Containerized services (Docker)
- Postgres + Redis + S3-compatible storage
- CI: GitHub Actions for builds and publishing artifacts
